567
00:45:56,240 --> 00:45:59,084
within 30 days prior
to their disappearance? If so, what for?

568
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:02,605
Evie's account is connected to ours.

569
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,683
She didn't withdraw any money.

570
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:07,525
Did you withdraw
more than $1,000 from your bank

571
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:10,490
within 30 days prior to the disappearance?
If so, what for?

572
00:46:13,880 --> 00:46:14,927
Yes.

573
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:18,845
If so, what for?

574
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,764
I was gonna leave John.

575
00:46:36,840 --> 00:46:42,688
You're surprised because we seem so happy.

576
00:46:49,240 --> 00:46:51,242
<i>My grandmother was born here.</i>

577
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:53,723
She lived here all her life.

578
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:57,724
She used to tell us kids
this place is chosen.

579
00:46:58,440 --> 00:47:01,967
The good Lord pointed His finger
down on the final day of creation

580
00:47:02,120 --> 00:47:05,010
and said, "You. The Jarden of Eden."

581
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:12,245
We didn't believe her,
but she said there was a way to prove it,

582
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:16,206
a way to make your wishes come true.

583
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:22,200
You take a bird,
you put it in a box and you bury it.

584
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:24,641
Anywhere in the woods is fine.

585
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,125
And you wait.

586
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:32,761
You wait three days, you come back,
dig it up, and if it's alive,

587
00:47:33,560 --> 00:47:36,166
right then is when you make your wish.

588
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:41,961
Little girls believe all sorts of things,
but I knew pretend when I heard it.

589
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:46,687
Birds living in the ground
for three days is pretend.

590
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:51,407
Making wishes is pretend.

591
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:57,001
The good Lord is pretend.

592
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:03,888
And then on October 14th,

593
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:07,810
people went away
from everywhere except here.

594
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:10,965
That was real.

595
00:48:11,800 --> 00:48:13,245
<i>That happened.</i>

596
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:18,521
<i>My grandma had been dead for 10 years,
but she was right.</i>

597
00:48:20,480 --> 00:48:22,289
This place was chosen.

598
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:29,920
And about a month ago,
I was walking out to my car

599
00:48:30,080 --> 00:48:31,764
and I saw it.

600
00:48:33,880 --> 00:48:38,602
A sparrow right by the driver's side door,

601
00:48:39,840 --> 00:48:42,571
lying there like it was
trying to get me to help it.

602
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:45,767
It was dehydrated.

603
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:47,691
Almost dead.

604
00:48:50,960 --> 00:48:53,691
You think I nursed it
back to health, Nora?

605
00:48:57,680 --> 00:49:02,811
Depending on the size of the box,
a bird can survive 20 hours.

606
00:49:03,960 --> 00:49:06,930
Anything over 30 hours
is medically impossible.

607
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:11,689
And like I said, this bird,
it didn't have anything left.

608
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,808
<i>So, I waited the three days.</i>

609
00:49:16,760 --> 00:49:20,890
I jogged out to the woods,
I dug up the box,

610
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:24,806
and I made my wish before I opened it.

611
00:49:27,640 --> 00:49:31,087
<i>I wished that my kids
would be okay if I left.</i>

612
00:49:32,320 --> 00:49:34,721
Because they had no idea I needed to go.

613
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:38,201
No idea what it's like to pretend.

614
00:49:41,440 --> 00:49:44,444
Michael, he has his faith.

615
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:46,766
He'd be fine.

616
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:49,851
But Evie...

617
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:54,083
She wouldn't understand.

618
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:57,169
It would break her heart.

619
00:49:58,680 --> 00:50:01,604
So, I wished
that she'd be okay without me.

620
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:08,524
I opened up the box,

621
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:11,810
the bird flew out.

622
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:17,560
And the next night my daughter was gone.

623
00:50:26,960 --> 00:50:28,962
Well, Erika, that's just...

624
00:50:31,280 --> 00:50:33,044
That's quite a stretch.

625
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:36,290
<i>Your logic, I'm sorry,</i>

626
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:39,603
<i>it's a little all over the place,
don't you think?</i>

627
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:43,604
Well, what do you think?

628
00:50:45,520 --> 00:50:48,171
You wanted to leave your husband.
Okay, so why didn't he go?

629
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:49,765
Why didn't you?

630
00:50:49,920 --> 00:50:52,605
A hundred and forty million people
disappeared three years ago.

631
00:50:52,760 --> 00:50:53,807
Did you wish them away, too?

632
00:50:53,960 --> 00:50:55,450
Because that's a lot
of birds to bury, Erika.

633
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,489
That's a flock of epic proportions.

634
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:03,125
I get it. I felt the same as you. I...

635
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:08,881
I felt responsible for losing my children.

636
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:11,048
I thought it was my fault.

637
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:14,843
But I moved past it.

638
00:51:16,200 --> 00:51:17,326
I evolved.

639
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:21,888
Because that's pathetic.

640
00:51:26,360 --> 00:51:28,840
Terrible things happen in this world.

641
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:33,401
And the only comfort we get
is that we didn't cause them.

642
00:51:34,520 --> 00:51:36,329
So, I'm sorry,

643
00:51:37,200 --> 00:51:39,726
but, Erika,
this had nothing to do with you.

644
00:51:52,160 --> 00:51:54,401
Did they depart or did they die?

645
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:57,206
What?

646
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:58,885
<i>Your children.</i>

647
00:52:00,200 --> 00:52:01,964
You said you lost them.

648
00:52:03,280 --> 00:52:05,965
Did they depart or did they die?

649
00:52:12,800 --> 00:52:14,290
They departed.

650
00:52:16,480 --> 00:52:22,487
What were the last words they said to you,
